# ANTI-PATTERN PREVENTION RULES

## Rule: No Self-Licking Ice Cream Cones
Every test MUST validate real business logic or real HTTP behavior. Violations:
- ❌ Testing that the test framework creates TestResult structs correctly
- ❌ Testing that colored output contains ANSI escape codes
- ❌ Mocking a function just to assert the mock was called
- ❌ Testing that TempDir creates a directory (tests tempfile, not our code)
- ❌ Assertion wrapper functions that add no value over direct assert!()
- ❌ Test helpers that exist only to be tested by other tests

Valid tests:
- ✅ Encrypt → decrypt → assert plaintext matches original
- ✅ Hash password → verify with correct password → Ok(true)
- ✅ POST /login with valid creds → assert redirect + Set-Cookie header
- ✅ Store encrypted setting → read raw DB → assert no plaintext visible
- ✅ Create expired session → run cleanup → assert session deleted

## Rule: No Circular Dependencies
- Core crates must NOT depend on test-runner or web framework
- Dependency flow: test-runner / api crate → core (one direction only)
- Core error uses plain types (e.g. u16 status) — framework conversion in api layer

## Rule: No Unnecessary Abstractions
- Do NOT create traits unless 2+ concrete types implement them
- Do NOT create wrapper types that only delegate to an inner type
- Do NOT create builder patterns for structs with <5 fields
- Do NOT create trait objects for single implementations
- The compression map IS the abstraction — do not layer another on top

## Rule: No Warning Suppression as a Fix
- The ONLY allowed #[allow(...)] is the tokenization-related allows:
  `non_camel_case_types, non_snake_case, dead_code, unused_imports`
- All other warnings must be fixed at the root cause
- If code is intentionally unused (reserved for future), add a comment explaining why

## Rule: No Hallucinated Data
- Never assume function return values — execute and verify
- Never fabricate test expected values — derive from actual execution
- Never assume database state — query and verify
- Read actual compiler errors before attempting fixes
